strings.Value: {n}This spot in the wall has been damaged by a fallen birch tree. The tops of the logs used to construct the wall have been broken, and the logs themselves stand askew. The thin birch tree still leans against it. A dexterous enough individual could probably climb up the trunk and get over the wall...{/n}
{n}The trunk of the birch tree is slippery, and the logs of the wall shift precariously under your weight, but you manage to make it over the wall.{/n}

{n}The moment you put pressure on the birch tree, you hear a deafening creak. Jumping back just in time, you see the trunk crack in half and fall â€” the inside had rotted through. It seems you have no choice but to go in through the front door.{/n}
